"The country was formed in 1795, when the warrior chief Kamehameha the Great, of the independent island of Hawaii, conquered the independent islands of Oahu, Maui, Molokai and Lnai and unified them under one government. In 1810, the whole Hawaiian archipelago became unified when Kauai and Niihau joined the Hawaiian Kingdom voluntarily. Two major dynastic families ruled the kingdom: the House of Kamehameha and the House of Kalkaua."
